==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Effluvium
<hw>Ef*flu"vi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Effluvia</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a flowing out, fr.
<ets>effluere</ets> to flow out. See <er>Effluent</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Subtile or invisible emanation; exhalation
perceived by the sense of smell; especially, noisome or noxious
exhalation; <as>as, the <ex>effluvium</ex> from diseased or putrefying
bodies, or from ill drainage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Efflux</ent>⟦br⟧
